{{zh-hanzi|[[御]][[宇]]}}
==Mandarin==
===Etymology===
From [[御]] to rule; to govern + [[宇]] everything under the heavens

===Verb===
{{cmn-verb|ts|pin=yùyǔ|pint=yu4yu3|rs=彳08}}
# (''archaic'') to rule over an empire; to sit on the throne
#* '''806:''' [[w:Bai Juyi|Bai Juyi]], ''[[wikisource:Song of Everlasting Regret|Song of Everlasting Regret]]''
#: [[漢]][[皇]][[重]][[色]][[思]][[傾國]]，'''御宇'''[[多]][[年]][[求]][[不得]]。 ([[Traditional Chinese|t]])
#: [[汉]][[皇]][[重]][[色]][[思]][[倾国]]，'''御宇'''[[多]][[年]][[求]][[不得]]。 ([[Simplified Chinese|s]])
#:: ''A certain emperor of the [[w:Han dynasty|Han dynasty]]<ref>A reference to the [[w:Emperor Xuanzong of Tang|Emperor Xuanzong of Tang]], whose relationship to [[w:Yang Guifei|Yang Guifei]] brought to mind the [[w:Emperor Wu of Han|Emperor Wu of Han]]'s relationship to his concubine, Consort Li.  Bai Juyi would have considered it unpoetic to refer to his subject directly.</ref> placed a premium on his dalliances, and longed for a beauty who could lay low an empire.  He '''sat on the throne''' for many years without finding such a beauty.''

<references />

